        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 24 at 6:30PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 630 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Many, or 21 miles north of Anacoco, moving northwest at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Many, Zwolle, Florien, Fisher, Negreet, Mount Carmel, and Belmont.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
